911-president-george-w-bush-consults-wit.ImageDescription:
PRESIDENT BUSH ARRIVES THE EMMA E. BOOKER ELEMENTARY SCHOOL FOR A READING PROGRAM DEMONSTRATION. HE CONFERS WITH STAFF IN A HOLDING ROOM PRIOR TO THE EVENT. STAFF MEMBERS  INCLUDE: ANDY CARD, DAN BARTLETT, ARI FLEISCHER AND GORDON JOHNDROE. THE PRESIDENT TALKS ON THE TELEPHONE WITH CONDOLEEZZA RICE ABOUT A PLANE THAT CRASHED INTO THE NORTH TOWER OF THE WORLD TRADE CENTER AT 8:48 A.M. (LATER IDENTIFIED AS HIJACKED AMERICAN AIRLINES FLIGHT 11). THE PRESIDENT PROCEEDS WITH THE EVENT AND READS TO STUDENTS IN A CLASSROOM (RELEASE P7060-19A). THE PRESIDENT CUTS SHORT THE EVENT TO WATCH TELEVISION COVERAGE OF A SECOND PLANE CRASHING INTO THE SOUTH TOWER OF THE WORLD TRADE CENTER (LATER IDENTIFIED AS HIJACKED UNITED AIRLINES FLIGHT 175). THE  PRESIDENT TALKS ON THE TELEPHONE WITH VP CHENEY, GOV. GEORGE PATAKI OF NEW YORK AND FBI DIRECTOR ROBERT MUELLER. DEBORAH LOEWER, NSC SETS UP PHONE CALLS. THE PRESIDENT DELIVERS REMARKS AT 9:30 A.M. REGARDING THE TERRORIST ATTACKS ON THE WORLD TRADE CENTER TWIN TOWERS. SHOWS THE PRESIDENT TALKING ON THE TELEPHONE AND WATCHING TELEVISION COVERAGE PRIOR TO HIS REMARKS (P7058-21A IS A WHITE HOUSE WEB SITE PHOTO). PRESIDENT BUSH  GREETS STUDENTS OUTSIDE THE SCHOOL. ALSO SHOWS CHILDREN IN SCHOOL UNIFORM WAVING  AT THE PRESIDENTIAL MOTORCADE.

RESTRICTED

Location: SARASOTA, FLORIDA

911-president-george-w-bush-at-world-ser.ImageDescription:
PRESIDENT BUSH AND LAURA BUSH ATTEND GAME THREE OF THE WORLD SERIES BETWEEN THE NEW YORK YANKEES AND THE ARIZONA DIAMONDBACKS AT YANKEE STADIUM. PRESIDENT BUSH  GREETS YANKEES OWNER GEORGE STEINBRENNER AND  MAYOR RUDOLPH GIULIANI IN THE PRACTICE BULLPEN. HE PUTS ON A VEST AND SWEATSHIRT. HE IS ASSISTED BY ANDY CARD AND LOGAN WALTERS (RESTRICTED). GEORGE TENET IS PRESENT.  THE PRESIDENT TAKES PITCHING PRACTICE. HE GIVES THE "THUMBS UP" FROM THE PITCHER'S MOUND AND THROWS OUT THE CEREMONIAL FIRST PITCH (JUMBO P9133-8, P9154-13). THE PRESIDENT AUTOGRAPHS BASEBALLS. HE HOLDS A BALL IN HIS HANDS (JUMBO P9151-15).  LAURA BUSH VISITS WITH GEORGE STEINBRENNER, DONALD TRUMP AND OTHERS AT THE STADIUM. STAFF PICTURED INCLUDE: KARL ROVE, LOGAN WALTERS, ERIC DRAPER, SARAH MOSS, ANDY CARD, CONDOLEEZZA RICE. INCLUDES POLICE GREETERS. THE PRESIDENT AND A POLICEMAN HOLD UP AN AUTOGRAPHED PHOTO OF THE PRESIDENT HOLDING UP A POLICE BADGE DURING A SPEECH.

Location: NEW YORK CITY

911-president-george-w-bush-visits-new-y.ImageDescription:
PRESIDENT BUSH ARRIVES THE DOWNTOWN MANHATTAN HELIPORT ABOARD MARINE ONE. HE IS ACCOMPANIED BY GOV. GEORGE PATAKI AND MAYOR RUDOLPH GIULIANI. THE PRESIDENT VISITS THE SITE OF THE WORLD TRADE CENTER DISASTER. HE GREETS FIREFIGHTERS, POLICE AND RESCUE PERSONNEL. THE PRESIDENT IS ACCOMPANIED BY NEW YORK FIRE DEPARTMENT COMMISSIONER THOMAS VON ESSEN, SEN. CHARLES (CHUCK) SCHUMER, SEN. HILLARY RODHAM CLINTON, REP. CHARLES (CHARLIE) RANGEL, FEMA DIRECTOR JOE ALLBAUGH, ANDY CARD, ARI FLEISCHER AND OTHERS. FORMER NYC MAYOR ED KOCH IS PRESENT. THE PRESIDENT USES A BULLHORN TO ADDRESS THE RESCUE WORKERS. HE PUTS HIS ARM AROUND RETIRED FIREMAN BOB BECKWITH FROM LADDER 117. HE WAVES THE AMERICAN FLAG (RELEASE, JUMBO P7376-22 IS ALSO A WHITE HOUSE WEB SITE PHOTO).  RESCUE WORKERS CHEER THE PRESIDENT (JUMBO, P7377-6 IS A WH WEB SITE PHOTO). TWO FIREMEN STAND AT GROUND ZERO (JUMBO P7377-13). THE PRESIDENT TOURS THE MURRAY STREET AND WEST STREET DISASTER SITE. HE VISITS WITH FAMILIES OF MISSING AND DECEASED EMERGENCY SERVICE WORKERS. HE GREETS FEMA AND RESCUE VOLUNTEERS AT THE JACOB K. JAVITS CONVENTION CENTER. ARLENE HOWARD PRESENTS THE PRESIDENT WITH HER SON'S POLICE BADGE (RELEASE P7385-16). PORT AUTHORITY POLICE OFFICER GEORGE HOWARD WAS WEARING THE BADGE WHEN HE WAS KILLED. PRESIDENT BUSH PUTS HIS ARMS AROUND AN UNIDENTIFIED COUPLE (JUMBO, RELEASE AND WH WEB SITE PHOTO P7385-12). THE PRESIDENT AUTOGRAPHS A BANNER. HE IS GIVEN AN AMERICAN FLAG AND A TEXAS STATE FLAG. PRESIDENT BUSH DEPARTS NEW YORK CITY ABOARD MARINE ONE. HE LOOKS DOWN AT THE NIGHTTIME RESCUE SITE.

Location: NEW YORK CITY                                                                   

Additional keywords: JUMBOS                          , RELEASE BOOK                    , WEB SITE
